In this article, President Biden meets with NATO Secretary General Stoltenberg in the Oval Office. They discuss NATO's relationship with Ukraine and the unity among NATO allies. They also talk about the support provided to Ukraine and the ongoing offensive against Russia. President Biden emphasizes the commitment of the United States to NATO's Article 5 and the importance of defense spending by allies. Secretary General Stoltenberg expresses gratitude for the support from the United States and other NATO members and highlights the significance of supporting Ukraine in order to prevent authoritarian leaders from using military force. They also discuss the upcoming NATO summit in Vilnius and the potential accession of Sweden into NATO. The article concludes with President Biden expressing appreciation for Secretary General Stoltenberg's leadership and commitment to the transatlantic bond.